BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:bZ4Q1RFwR3H44NF14pY3G
SUMMARY:MOHAI Mercantile Literary Series - Seattle's Locks and Ship Canal
DTSTAMP:20260318T135140Z
DTSTART:20260324T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:MOHAI Mercantile is proud to host the official book launch even
	t for Seattle’s Locks and Ship Canal with local historians David B. Willia
	ms and Jennifer Ott! \\nThis portable guide from UW Press and HistoryLink 
	is an introduction to the engineering marvel of the Ballard locks\\\, and 
	a primer on the history of the ship canal. Hear from the authors about the
	 tumultuous history of one of Seattle’s defining projects\\\, and the dram
	atic changes it brought to the city’s economy\\\, neighborhoods\\\, and na
	tural environment. \\nDoors open at 6pm for music and mingling. Food and d
	rink available for purchase. \\nConversation and Q&A begin at 7pm\\\, foll
	owed by a book signing with the authors. \\nPreorder your copy through the
	 MOHAI Mercantile beginning in January 2026!\n\nhttps://mohai.org/event/mo
	hai-mercantile-literary-series-seattles-locks-and-ship-canal/\n\nFrom MOHA
	I - Museum of History & Industry
URL:https://mohai.org/event/mohai-mercantile-literary-series-seattles-locks
	-and-ship-canal/
LOCATION:Faye G. Allen Grand Atrium\\\, MOHAI 860 Terry Ave N\\\, Seattle\\
	\, WA\\\, 98109\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:mohai
CATEGORIES:MOHAI - Museum of History & Industry
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
